post_text: We hope that our APSB students, staff and parents are safe during this clean up process. Electricity is beginning to be restored to some parts of our district. Due to damage and most of the parish being without power, Allen Parish Schools will remain closed until further notice.
text: We hope that our APSB students, staff and parents are safe during this clean up process. Electricity is beginning to be restored to some parts of our district. Due to damage and most of the parish being without power, Allen Parish Schools will remain closed until further notice.

post_text:
Allen Parish Schools will remain closed due to repairs and loss of electricity. Continue to check our website and Facebook page for updates.
Our thoughts go out to students, staff, and parents of Allen Parish School Board. We hope everyone is safe.

Allen Parish School System Update:

Food pick up will be from 10:30-12:00 on Thursday, April 9 at Kinder High, Reeves High, Oberlin High, Fairview High, Oakdale High, and Elizabeth High.

Any student up to 18 years old or 21 for Sped. Students who attend Allen Parish schools need not be present but their names must be provided.

Children who do not attend Allen Parish Schools must be present or parent must provide birth certificate.

We are hoping to have meals delivered to each site by 10 am.

Our next meal hand out date will be Monday, April 20 at the same times.

post_text:
2018-2019 Allen Parish Early Childhood Network Performance Profile Scores released!
The APECCN received a score of High Proficient and ranks number ten in the state in comparison to 65 other early childhood networks! Two sites were recognized at the November Allen Parish School Board meeting. Congratulations to Kids R Us Childcare Center as a Birth to Three Honor Roll recipient. Teacher, Ms. Samantha Bryant and Center Director, Ms. Vergie Christian accepted this honor. Congratulations to Oberlin Elementary in making the Excellent Honor Roll. Administrator, Ms. Elizabeth Faulk, teachers, Ms. Blaire Buller along with Miss Kama Guillory, and former administrator Ms. Misty Alexander accepted the honor for their school.
